title: Microsoft Azure Virtual Network Gateways: Connections
agents: azure
catalog: cloud/azure
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors Microsoft Azure virtual network gateways.
 Monitored metrics are number of Point-to-site connections,
 Point-to-site bandwidth, Site-to-site bandwidth, the input
 and the output of a tunnel and the number of the input and output
 packets dropped.

 You can configure levels for these metrics using the rule "Azure VNet Gateway".
 In order to use this check, you need to configure the Azure special agent.

item:
 The name of the resource.

discovery:
 One service is created for each virtual network gateway.
